ten Werkes schreibt die Praxis der Neuregelungen durch das ESUG fort, verschafft Insolvenzpraktikern und Beratern einen fundierten Überblick und präsentiert professionelle Umsetzungsmöglichkeiten. Neue Kapitel ergänzen das breit aufgestelle Werk weiter und befassen sich u.a. mit der Umwandlung im Insolvenzplan und dem Reverse Debt Equity Swap.  aThis new edition describes practices under the regulations of the ESUG (Insolvency Law Reform Act), providing legal professionals and advisors a thorough overview of the law, including options for implementation. New chapters enhance the broadly conceived work to address numerous issues, including the conversion of a firm’s legal form during insolvency as well as reverse debt equity swaps.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aLAW / Business & Financial.2bisacsh1 aKübler, Bruno M., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2014z9783110370232oZDB-23-DGC0 cEPUBz978381455416740uhttps://doi.org/10.15375/978381455700740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783814557007423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783814557007.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2014  aZDB-23-DGGb2014